<task id="GUID-BED80320-70E5-47C4-9530-CC26073D469D" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title id="GUID-71E6E7FF-D420-465A-9CFA-86F8BA5BE094">Log Purge</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>administration<indexterm>log purge</indexterm></indexterm>This feature
                allows users to manage the volume of log files for optimizing StellarOne's disk
                space usage.</p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_pt3_g3m_m5b">
            <step>
                <cmd>Go to <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Log Purge</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>There are two ways for log purge settings. Users can choose from either one
                    listed below:</cmd>
                <choices id="choices_nxv_vwn_m5b">
                    <choice><uicontrol>Purge Now</uicontrol>:<p>Use this setting to purge logs
                            immediately.</p><ol id="ol_ovg_bxn_m5b">
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the drop-down menu next to the <uicontrol>Purge</uicontrol>
                                    title, and then select the log types to be purged.</p>
                                <ul id="ul_yrr_hxn_m5b">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>All Logs</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>System Log, Audit Log, Server Events, or Agent Events</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the drop-down menu next to the <uicontrol>older
                                        than</uicontrol> title, and then select a specified time
                                    frame. The files older than the time frame will be removed.</p>
                                <ul id="ul_pvh_kyn_m5b">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>No limit</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>1 month(s), 2 months(s), 3 months(s), 6 months(s), 12
                                            months(s), 18 months(s), 24 months(s), 36 months(s), 48
                                            months(s), 60 months(s)</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the drop-down menu next to the <uicontrol>Keep at
                                        most</uicontrol> title, and then select the maximum number
                                    of log entries to keep.</p>
                                <ul id="ul_fm1_yyn_m5b">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>0 entries</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>10,000 entries, 50,000 entries, 100,000 entries, 500,000
                                            entries, 1,000,000 entries, 5,000,000 entries,
                                            10,000,000 entries</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the <uicontrol>Purge</uicontrol> button, and the event logs
                                    will be immediately purged.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol></choice>
                    <choice><uicontrol>Automatic Purge</uicontrol>: <p>Use this setting to set an
                            automatic purge once per day.</p><ol id="ol_mz3_kzn_m5b">
                            <li>
                                <p>Specify the log types you wan to purge: <uicontrol>System
                                        Log</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Audit Log</uicontrol>,
                                        <uicontrol>Server Events</uicontrol>, or <uicontrol>Agent
                                        Events</uicontrol>.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the drop-down menu next to the <uicontrol>older
                                        than</uicontrol> title, and then select a specified time
                                    frame. The files older than the time frame will be removed.</p>
                                <ul id="ul_d3l_p14_m5b">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>No limit</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>1 month(s), 2 months(s), 3 months(s), 6 months(s), 12
                                            months(s), 18 months(s), 24 months(s), 36 months(s), 48
                                            months(s), 60 months(s)</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the drop-down menu next to the <uicontrol>Keep at
                                        most</uicontrol> title, and then select the maximum number
                                    of log entries to keep.</p>
                                <ul id="ul_l3s_q14_m5b">
                                    <li>
                                        <p>0 entries</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>10,000 entries, 50,000 entries, 100,000 entries, 500,000
                                            entries, 1,000,000 entries, 5,000,000 entries,
                                            10,000,000 entries</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click the <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol> button, and the event logs
                                    will be automatically purged once per day.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol></choice>
                </choices>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
